  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heavy rainfall in the third week of January produced severe flooding in the town of S&#xE1;enz Pe&#xF1;a, Chaco.

On Saturday 20/01, 297 millimeters of rain fell in a span of three hours. These values are well above the usual level of precipitation. To these values must be added the 75 millimeters that had accumulated during the rains on Thursday 18/01. Excess rainfall, coupled with poor soil permeability, which generated several neighborhoods of the city are affected to varying degrees.

Current weather forecasts report that weather conditions would improve, just for Thursday afternoon 25/01. In this context it is expected that the drainage of water surplus in the affected area occurs more slowly.

As a result, the municipal and provincial authorities activated their emergency protocols.</narrative>
  </description>
